ore disappointing is the fact that Seagal never fights in hand to hand combat with the film 's chief villains , tis a shame . He does n't even snap a wrist or crack a neck in any visible way( .. sure we see a slight resemblance of some tool getting tossed around , but it 's not as clear a picture as I enjoy because the filmmakers have such fast edits and dizzying close - ups ) .
