0 Carly Pope plays JJ , a newly promoted Food Critic whose flamboyant , overbearing mother moves in with her . JJ , aghast at this turn of events , then blackmails restaurant owner , Alex , to entertain her mother in exchange for " maybe " reviewing his dying restaurant . Alex predictably falls for the daughter while warming to the mother . There are numerous problems with this movie , the characters are universally 2-dimensional . JJ is a self - serving , hateful character , her mother superficial and shallow . JJ 's colleagues at the magazine are bitchy and opportunistic . The underlying message of an over-50 woman unable to make it on her own , without male assistance is bad , bad , BAD . The acting is uniformly dull , the script uninspired . The films only saving grace is the setting of New York City . I would so NOT recommend this film .
